        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a generic KubeVirt provider that provisions Linux VM leases through `kubectl`, connects through `virtctl`, and supports configurable templates, namespaces, SSH forwarding, lifecycle cleanup, status, inspect, VNC, and slug/claim scoping\n- add a versioned external executable provider protocol so private VM/devbox control planes can integrate through configuration without provider-specific Crabbox forks\n- keep provider routing state private per lease while preserving reproducible SSH, retry, and stop commands without leaking external provider secrets\n- harden shared-lease mutation auth and document KubeVirt, external providers, WebVNC support boundaries, config, protocol, lifecycle, routing, and failure recovery\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go vet ./... && go test -race ./... && scripts/test-go-modules.sh && scripts/check-go-coverage.sh 90.0 && go build -trimpath -o /tmp/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox && node --test scripts/*.test.js && scripts/check-docs.sh && git diff --check origin/main...HEAD && git diff --check`\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker && npm run lint --prefix worker && npm run check --prefix worker && npm test --prefix worker && npm run build --prefix worker`\n- local autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Live infrastructure\n\n- AWS metal live e2e passed with `bin/crabbox run --provider aws --type c5.metal --market on-demand --ttl 45m --idle-timeout 10m --stop-after always --script /tmp/crabbox-kubevirt-metal-e2e.sh`\n- outer run `run_afc227f6e170`, outer lease `cbx_05a663716d3b`, AWS `c5.metal`, cleaned up with `lease cleanup stopped=true policy=always`\n- nested KubeVirt smoke used kind `v1.35.5`, KubeVirt `v1.8.3`, inner lease `cbx_9f6e78087a26`, slug `kv-smoke-45205`, VM `crabbox-kv-smoke-45205-7ef431ac`\n- warmup `1m6.221s`, inner status/inspect ready, remote command exit 0, total outer runtime `5m25.972s`\n",
